  "prompt": "Is it illegal that paying cash to buy car or house?",
  "response": "Paying cash for a car or house is not inherently illegal, but there are some important considerations:\n\nCar Purchase:\n1. Legally, you can pay cash for a car\n2. Large cash transactions may require reporting to authorities\n3. Dealerships might have their own policies about cash payments\n\nHouse Purchase:\n1. Paying cash for a house is legal\n2. Large cash transactions over $10,000 must be reported to the IRS\n3. Banks and title companies will typically require documentation for anti-money laundering purposes\n\nGeneral Rules:\n- Transactions over $10,000 in cash must be reported\n- Large cash payments may trigger additional scrutiny\n- You'll need to provide proof of funds and source of money\n- Some sellers might prefer other payment methods\n\nIf you're making a large cash transaction, it's recommended to:\n- Keep documentation\n- Work with a reputable financial institution\n- Be prepared to explain the source of funds\n- Consult with a financial advisor or lawyer if needed",
